<br>
First I would like to point out that contacting a leader even if it is about a leader is never foolish.  Shortly after I was contacted Roren left and the situation ended, or so I thought.  All I knew at that time was that he had not been invited to attend a raid and was being an ass.  While I myself am not a person that is quick to use profanity or show anger, I have seen many in this game do so.  It is stupid when someone goes on acting like roren did that night, and there is no excuse for it.  But I am sure you have had members of your guild also behave in a less than exemplary way before, and I am sure it sucked for you that they dragged your guild tag and all of your reputations through the mud.  So I ask you to ask yourself, was this really an example of our whole guild, or was it the actions of one wayward individual?<br>
<br>
It is true I guess that roren is an officer.  I honestly was not aware he was since I have only been the guild leader for a year.  The past guild leader was fond of handing out officer ships and tracking everyone down to remove it is a pain and micromanagement I would rather not have to perform.  <br>
<br>
I usually prefer not to punish or remove individuals from the guild, because I have come to realize that in most cases the people a member has sinned against will usually effectively punish them enough.  I believe in this case you have punished Roren enough for me to feel he now understands how stupid he really was that night.  And so there is no need for me to punish him more, though I may track him down and remove the officer status from him if I can figure out how.  That is not to say that if you feel he hasn’t been punished enough you shouldn’t go on doing it.  But again I have to ask you to put yourselves in his shoes and ask yourself if you have ever done anything really incredibly dumb that you regretted the next day.  <br>
<br>
It is true I was asked to go to someone after the raid, but at that time I didn’t realize the situation was so bad and so I figured it was best just to drop it and move on with my enjoyment of EQ.  It is after all a game that is meant to be enjoyed, and usually being the leader of a relatively large guild like warders has a way of interfering with that and so I choose to enjoy as much as I possibly can.  <br>
<br>
Summary:<br>
What roren did was bad, and I think he gets that now.  Since Roren was the only member of warders involved it is somewhat unfair to hold the rest of us accountable.  If anyone wants to discuss this with me further, seek me in game I am usually playing as aerch or creh these days.<br>
